I put the version as 2.6.9 because that was the latest version it would let me select but my current SourceTree version is 2.6.10.0.

When I create a pull request from within SourceTree it will open a 404 error page on Bitbucket. If you look at the address it has two slashes after the main domain.
{code:java}
https://bitbucket.org//*******/learngit/pull-request/new?source=*******/learngit:e8227bc6c7ee:release%2f1.2
{code}
Clicking the "Remote" button on the top right-hand corner brings you to another 404 error page on Bitbucket with the same issue. The URL has two slashes after the main domain address.
{code:java}
https://bitbucket.org//*******/learngit
{code}

On the commit screen, the text above the commit message field that says something like:

{code}
FirstName Lastname <email@example.com>
{code}

is white text on a light gray background. It is very hard to read.

Rather than opening a new terminal and running {{cd <directory>}}, SourceTree should simply use:
{code}
NSWorkspace.shared.openFile(<directory>, withApplication: "Terminal")
{code}
in Swift, or:
{code}
[[NSWorkspace sharedWorkspace] openFile:<directory> withApplication:@"Terminal"];
{code}
in Objective-C. This makes the output cleaner and is more stable. This way could also support using 3rd party Terminal utilities.

