h3. Problem Definition
* It is currently not possible to hide the JIRA User Timezone Difference Warning. 
* Some users would choose to use a different Timzone for multiple reasons one of it being this bug : https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-44363
* It is only possible to hide the JIRA User Timezone Difference Warning for JIRA 6.3 and older following this KB : https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/How+to+hide+JIRA+User+Timezone+Difference+Warning 
* Unfortunately it is no possible with JIRA 6.4 and later as there are changes in the code. In JIRA 6.3 and older , the timezone warning message had an ID named {{timezoneDiffBanner}} which can be hidden using script but in JIRA 6.4 onwards, this ID has been removed and replaced with a universal ID for all banner messages {{aui-flag-container}}

h3. Suggested Solution
Make it possible to  hide the JIRA User Timezone Difference Warning. 
 
h3. Workaround 
* You can still hide the Timezone difference warning by adding this script to the Announcement banner :
{code}
<style type="text/css">
  #aui-flag-container{ display:none; }
</style>
{code}
* However this will also hide all other warnings which is not feasible.

