Having a following piece of code using a Java7 multiple-catch language feature:

{code:java}
try { 
   //...
} catch (FirstException|SecondException e) {
  throw e;
}
{code}

Clover will make code instrumentation like this:
{code:java}
} catch (FirstException|SecondException e) {
    __CLR3_1_6cch31flqx6.R.inc(28);throw e;
}
{code}

The problem is that we know that exception was caught, be we don't know whether it was FirstException or SecondException type. Clover does not support branch coverage in catch statements. 

I would be nice to have this information as well, similarly as we've got in conditional expressions, like:

{code:java}
if (exceptionName.equals("First"))
{code}

is being translated to:
{code:java}
if ((((exceptionName.equals("First"))&&
(__CLR3_1_6cch31flqx6.R.iget(24)!=0|true))||
(__CLR3_1_6cch31flqx6.R.iget(25)==0&false))) 
{code}

